  "recipe_notes": [
    "I am using American cheese for this recipe. You can also use Swiss cheese, colby jack, havarti, and other kinds of cheese that melts well.",
    "Boneless chicken breasts are ideal to make chicken tenders. You can also prepare this in advance by brining. This process will give you flavorful and moist chicken tenders.",
    "I find Dijon mustard helpful in adding flavor to my chicken tenders. This is an optional ingredient. I suggest that you try it though to see if this is for you.",
    "Panko breadcrumbs will give your chicken tenders that nice crispy texture. However, you can also use regular bread crumbs or Italian breadcrumbs for this recipe."
  ],
